The paper compares learning-based methods and classical methods for navigation in virtual environments, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses collision avoidance, memory management, and handling ambiguity and noise, which are topics related to Computer Vision (cs.CV), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI and cs.RO, followed by cs.CV, cs.LG, and cs.HC.
